simulation function

runSimulation5.4.Rd

this is the simulation function

runSimulation5.4(
  recip_matrix,
  donor_matrix,
  algorithm_FUN,
  eligible_FUN,
  matching_FUN,
  waitlist_FUN,
  national_algorithm_threshold = 5.4e+07,
  state_algorithm = TRUE,
  state_algorithm_FUN = NULL,
  state_eligible_FUN = NULL,
  state_matching_FUN = NULL,
  resampleN = 20,
  num_donor = 800,
  num_recip = 300,
  parallel = FALSE,
  ncores = 2,
  verbose = TRUE,
  waitlist_arg = list(waitlist_Risk = TRUE, rate_in = 0.7, rate_out = 0.4,
    yearly_scale_in = c(sort(1 + rexp(length(tx_date_ranges), 1/0.1))), yearly_scale_out
    = c(sort(runif(length(tx_date_ranges), 0.3, 1), decreasing = TRUE))),
  eligible_arg = list(AB_priority = TRUE),
  state_eligible_arg = list(),
  matching_arg = list(),
  state_matching_arg = list(),
  state_balance = TRUE,
  dynamic_waitlist = TRUE,
  National_II = TRUE
)

Arguments

algorithm_FUN

this is the allocation algorithm
eligible_FUN

this is the eligible recipient pool function
matching_FUN

this is the selection function
waitlist_FUN

this is the waiting list function
national_algorithm_threshold

give the threshold number to run national-state algorithm
state_algorithm

whether to have state algorithm or not
state_algorithm_FUN

state algorithm function
state_eligible_FUN

state eligible function
state_matching_FUN

state matching function
resampleN

number of simulation results
num_donor

number of donor
num_recip

number of recipients
parallel

to run paralel or not
ncores

number of cores
verbose

verbose indicator
waitlist_arg

arguments for the wl
eligible_arg

arguments for the eligible pool
state_eligible_arg

arguments for the state eligible pool
matching_arg

arguments for matching functions
state_matching_arg

arguments for state matching functions
state_balance

state balance adjustment indicator
dynamic_waitlist

whether to have dynamic wl or not
National_II

national algorithm round two indicator

Value

allo_score, which is the alocation score for each new pair

Examples

data("newdata", package = "KidneyAllocation")
